H0.text: If North is 0 and 360 degrees and East is 90 degrees, how many degrees is South-West. 180 degrees

H1.text: If North is 0 and 360 degrees and East is 90 degrees, how many degrees is South-West. 270 degrees

H2.text: If North is 0 and 360 degrees and East is 90 degrees, how many degrees is South-West. 45 degrees

H3.text: If North is 0 and 360 degrees and East is 90 degrees, how many degrees is South-West. 225 degrees

A4.text: Eight-point compass roses use the eight principal winds—that is, the four cardinal directions (N, E, S, W) plus the four 'intercardinal' or getMenuInflater directions (NE, SE, SW, NW), at angles of difference of 45°.
